The paper deals with the problem of manipulating objects in a cluttered space, which is a common problem in robotics. The paper proposes a method that leverages ideas from algorithmic theory, multi-robot motion planning, and manipulation planning to propose appropriate graphical representations for this challenge. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to evaluate the approach, which suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of computer vision techniques to retrieve a particular object from a shelf, which suggests that it could belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper deals with the problem of manipulating multiple objects, which suggests that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a method that allows for precomputation, which suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
